{
  "doc_id": "28307",
  "text": "Effect of ␣-synuclein mutations on ␣-synuclein aggregation ␣-Synuclein aggregation into Lewy bodies is a hallmark of PD and other neurodegenerative disorders [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , raising the question how various ␣-synuclein mutations may alter ␣-synuclein aggregation. To assess the aggregation of WT and mutant ␣-synucleins in an intracellular environment, we overexpressed WT and mutant ␣-synucleins in HEK293T cells and measured the amount of protein produced using quantitative immunoblotting (Fig.  7A,B) . We then used immunostaining with antibodies to the myc epitope-tag on the expressed ␣-synuclein proteins to quantify the formation of ␣-synuclein aggregates (Fig.  7C-E) . ",
